HEADWORD: Derecho
<hw>De*re"cho</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp.
<ets>derecho</ets> straight.]</ety> <def>A straight wind without
apparent cyclonic tendency, usually accompanied with rain and often
destructive, common in the prairie regions of the United
States.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

